tasks.description:
In `collect_all_requirements` (crates/reify-compiler/src/lib.rs:4546-4558), the depth-limit check fires BEFORE the visited-set check. This means:

1. When depth > MAX_TRAIT_DEPTH, the trait is NOT inserted into `state.visited`
2. If the same deep trait is reachable via multiple paths (diamond pattern), each path emits its own "too deep" diagnostic — duplicate errors

Fix: Swap the two guards so the visited check comes first. Insert `trait_name` into `state.visited` before the depth check. This ensures duplicate paths silently skip already-processed traits.

```rust
// BEFORE (current):
if depth > MAX_TRAIT_DEPTH { ... return; }
if !state.visited.insert(trait_name.to_string()) { return; }

// AFTER (fixed):
if !state.visited.insert(trait_name.to_string()) { return; }
if depth > MAX_TRAIT_DEPTH { ... return; }
```

